The paper discusses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization and decision-making, which are common themes in neural networks and control systems, respectively. Hence, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper introduces a new R package for reinforcement learning, which falls under the scope of computational mathematics and optimization, making cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) another potential sub-category.
